description: From be- (“around, about”) +‎ dwell. Compare Middle Dutch bedwellen.

verbs.description: bedwell (third-person singular simple present bedwells, present participle bedwelling, simple past and past participle bedwelt)

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive) To dwell around or about (a place); inhabit.
examples: Gentry of narrow income used to bedwell Montreuil; they are gone, war, want or death knows where.
